-- Arrk shares up by daily limit as Orix considers deal
-- 
-- Sun Jun 22, 2014 08:38PM EDT
-- None



TOKYO, June 23 (Reuters) - Shares in Japanese automobile prototype maker Arrk Corp <7873.T> were flooded with buy orders and rose by their daily limit to 285 yen in early trade on Monday after leasing firm Orix Corp <8591.T> said it was considering an acquisition of the company.

Public broadcaster NHK said Orix planned to buy most of the company's shares for 15 billion yen ($147 million).